<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747163>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. (a–c), Escharifora argus d’Orbigny; syntypes, MNHN.F.A24605; Cretaceous, Senonian (probably Maastrichtian), Néhou, Manche, Normandy, France; (a) fragment of small branch; (b) avicularium; (c) part of a branch showing autozooids and avicularia. (d–f), Escharifora circe d’Orbigny; NHMUK BZ 339(a); Cretaceous, Campanian, Biron Formation, Caillaud, Charente Maritime, France; (d) centre of bifoliate branch; (e) autozooidal opesia surrounded by pitted cryptocyst; (f) ovicellate autozooid. Scale bars: a, c, d = 1 mm; b = 200 µm; e, f = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747163/files/figure.png" .

